2
0:00:18.26,000 --> 0:00:21,000
I have a studio in London

3
0:00:21.26,000 --> 0:00:23,000
that has a particular approach

4
0:00:23.26,000 --> 0:00:25,000
to designing buildings.

5
0:00:25.26,000 --> 0:00:27,000
When I was growing up,

6
0:00:27.26,000 --> 0:00:3,000
I was exposed to making

7
0:00:30.26,000 --> 0:00:33,000
and crafts and materials

8
0:00:33.26,000 --> 0:00:35,000
and invention on a small scale.

9
0:00:35.26,000 --> 0:00:37,000
And I was there looking

10
0:00:37.26,000 --> 0:00:39,000
at the larger scale of buildings

11
0:00:39.26,000 --> 0:00:41,000
and finding

12
0:00:41.26,000 --> 0:00:43,000
that the buildings that were around me

13
0:00:43.26,000 --> 0:00:46,000
and that were being designed

14
0:00:46.26,000 --> 0:00:5,000
and that were there in the publications I was seeing

15
0:00:50.26,000 --> 0:00:53,000
felt soulless and cold.

16
0:00:53.26,000 --> 0:00:55,000
And there on the smaller scale,

17
0:00:55.26,000 --> 0:00:57,000
the scale of an earring

18
0:00:57.26,000 --> 0:00:59,000
or a ceramic pot

19
0:00:59.26,000 --> 0:01:01,000
or a musical instrument,

20
0:01:01.26,000 --> 0:01:04,000
was a materiality and a soulfulness.

21
0:01:04.26,000 --> 0:01:08,000
And this influenced me.

22
0:01:08.26,000 --> 0:01:11,000
The first building I built was 20 years ago.

23
0:01:11.26,000 --> 0:01:13,000
And since, in the last 20 years,

24
0:01:13.26,000 --> 0:01:15,000
I've developed a studio in London.

25
0:01:15.26,000 --> 0:01:17,000
Sorry, this was my mother, by the way,

26
0:01:17.26,000 --> 0:01:19,000
in her bead shop in London.

27
0:01:19.26,000 --> 0:01:22,000
I spent a lot of time counting beads and things like that.

28
0:01:22.26,000 --> 0:01:25,000
I'm just going to show, for people who don't know my studio's work,

29
